body:
RTL does not appear to be checking that the number of arguments returned by InstanceOp match the module it is referencing.  The following does not produce an error:

```mlir
// RUN: circt-opt ./test.mlir

rtl.module @empty() -> () {
  rtl.output
}

rtl.module @test() -> () {
  // too many outputs
  %0, %1, %3 = rtl.instance "inline-me" @mem() : () -> (i2, i2, i2)
  rtl.output
}
```
